humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that there is metastatic carcinoma in the sentinel lymph node (SLNB) and no metastases in the remaining level I and II axillary lymph nodes (Level I: 3/9; Level II: 0/7). This corresponds to N1 as per Rule 12: N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes (No/Total).

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient was found to have metastatic carcinoma in the sentinel lymph node (level I) and a total of 3 out of 9 lymph nodes were positive in level I. No metastatic carcinoma was found in level II (0 out of 7 lymph nodes). Therefore, the N stage is N1 (N1mi, if there is no extranodal extension of carcinoma, or N1a, if there is extranodal extension of carcinoma). Since the report does not mention extranodal extension, I will assume N1mi.
